                    <td bgcolor="#fffff" valign="top" style="background-color: #ffffff;"><!-- TemplateBeginEditable name="content" --><p>Hey Bruce,</p>
<p>Today is your last chance to get your name on the record against&#160;Quebec&rsquo;s Internet censorship law, Bill 74, which censors the Internet, and violates our right to free expression.<sup>1, 2, 3</sup></p>
<p>Tomorrow, OpenMedia will be submitting our comments to federal decision-makers asserting that the controversial bill is unconstitutional&#160;&ndash; and we want to include your voice.&#160;If enough people speak out by <a href="http://qb.salsalabs.com/dia/track.jsp?v=2&c=HFuLrTop1jTsHjwXZ3b4g0%2FkFGQdT81T">endorsing this letter</a>, then the federal government will tell Quebec lawmakers they have no choice but to&#160;repeal this problematic law.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><font color="#0000ee"><b><u>You only have 24 hours to add your name to our letter</u></b></font><a href="http://qb.salsalabs.com/dia/track.jsp?v=2&c=AxjM3POUQ825Z%2BHhfY4LP0%2FkFGQdT81T"><b>&#160;speaking out against Bill 74, Bruce.</b></a></p>
<p>The Bill is being challenged in the Quebec Superior Court now by Internet service providers and consumer advocates.<sup>4 </sup>It goes against Section 36 of the Telecommunications Act,<sup>5</sup> and breaks the rules that keep our Internet free and open.</p>
<p>What&rsquo;s worse, Bill 74 is a slippery slope &mdash; no government should have the power to decide what its citizens can and cannot view online. Once governments are given this power, what is to stop them from censoring more and more content as it suits their interests?</p>
<p>We submit our letter tomorrow, Bruce. The more names we have <a href="http://qb.salsalabs.com/dia/track.jsp?v=2&c=VeMXikkpmFADP2fmNDB3K2nkiQWFAUew">endorsing our call</a> asking the Quebec government to repeal the law, the stronger our letter will be received.</p>
<p>Please, <a href="http://qb.salsalabs.com/dia/track.jsp?v=2&c=QX%2B85rfOWW5fAtldatlJ7GnkiQWFAUew"><b>sign the petition right now</b></a> to tell the federal government: <b>"Quebec lawmakers must&#160;</b><b>repeal Bill 74&rsquo;s site-blocking provisions &mdash; they are in violation of federal law and the principle of Net Neutrality.&rdquo;</b></p>
<p>Thank you,</p>
<p>&mdash;Katy, and your OpenMedia team</p>
<p><i>P.S. Every dollar we receive goes a long way to help our small team stand up for an open and free Internet, Bruce. <a href="http://qb.salsalabs.com/dia/track.jsp?v=2&c=nQRuklHH7hqDYvv839O390%2FkFGQdT81T">Consider donating even $5 now. </a></i></p>
